<li id="cite_note-169"><b><a href="#cite_ref-169" title="">^</a></b> For association with the five faces and other groups of five, see: Kramrisch, p. 182.</li>
<li id="cite_note-170"><b><a href="#cite_ref-170" title="">^</a></b> For the epithets <i><span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn">pañcamukha</span></i> and <i><span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn">pañcavaktra</span></i>, both of which mean "five faces", as epithets of <span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn">Śiva</span>, see: Apte, p. 578, middle column.</li>
