<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFStutley1985">Stutley, Margaret (1985). <i>The Illustrated Dictionary of Hindu Iconography</i>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Illustrated+Dictionary+of+Hindu+Iconography&amp;rft.aulast=Stutley&amp;rft.aufirst=Margaret&amp;rft.au=Stutley%2C+Margaret&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Shiva"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> First Indian Edition: Munshiram Manoharlal, 2003, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/8121510872" class="internal">ISBN 81-215-1087-2</a>.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTattwananda1984">Tattwananda, Swami (1984). <i>Vaisnava Sects, Saiva Sects, Mother Worship</i>. Calcutta: Firma KLM Private Ltd..</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Vaisnava+Sects%2C+Saiva+Sects%2C+Mother+Worship&amp;rft.aulast=Tattwananda&amp;rft.aufirst=Swami&amp;rft.au=Tattwananda%2C+Swami&amp;rft.date=1984&amp;rft.place=Calcutta&amp;rft.pub=Firma+KLM+Private+Ltd.&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Shiva"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> First revised edition.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFZimmer1946">Zimmer, Heinrich (1946). <i>Myths and Symbols in Indian Art and Civilization</i>. Princeton, New Jersey: Princeton University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691017786" class="internal">ISBN 0-691-01778-6</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Myths+and+Symbols+in+Indian+Art+and+Civilization&amp;rft.aulast=Zimmer&amp;rft.aufirst=Heinrich&amp;rft.au=Zimmer%2C+Heinrich&amp;rft.date=1946&amp;rft.place=Princeton%2C+New+Jersey&amp;rft.pub=Princeton+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-691-01778-6&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Shiva"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> First Princeton-Bollingen printing, 1972.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><i>Hanuman Chalisa</i>. Chennai, India: Sri Ramakrishna Math. 1985. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/8171200869" class="internal">ISBN 81-7120-086-9</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Hanuman+Chalisa&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft.place=Chennai%2C+India&amp;rft.pub=Sri+Ramakrishna+Math&amp;rft.isbn=81-7120-086-9&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Shiva"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
